Telkom has told its shareholders it received written notice from the Cell C board of directors rejecting its non-binding proposal. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Cell C has formally rejected Telkom's takeover bid. Telkom has told its shareholders it received written notice from the Cell C board of directors rejecting its non-binding proposal. It's understood Telkom's offer was one of two being considered by Cell C, the other being a broader roaming agreement with MTN. READ: Telkom confirms it wants to buy Cell C Telkom's offer was thrown into doubt after Cell C entered into a roaming agreement with MTN earlier this month. Cell C and Telkom grouping would have created a strong competitor to Vodacom and MTN. MTN and Vodacom have 70-million of the 95-million active SIM cards in SA.